<P>&startq;Why, that's the rea&s;on,&endq; &s;aid Indiana, &startq;he wants
to marry you to cou&s;in Eugenia; becau&s;e, he &s;ays, it's
to make you amends.&endq;</P>
<P>This led him to a rather more &s;erious con&s;ideration
of the affair; for, he prote&s;ted the money was what
he could not do without. Yet, again parading to the
